quran[33]{c,v,t}:
  55,46,But for those that fear the majesty of their Lord there are two Gardens
  55,47,so which of your Lord‘s blessings would you deny
  55,48,planted with shady trees
  55,49,So which of your Lord‘s blessings would you deny
  55,50,Each is watered by a flowing spring
  55,51,Which of your Lord‘s blessings would you deny
  55,52,Each bears every kind of fruit in pairs
  55,53,So which of your Lord‘s blessings would you deny
  55,54,"They shall recline on couches lined with rich brocade, and within reach will hang the fruits of both Gardens"
  55,55,So which of your Lord‘s blessings would you deny
  55,56,Therein are bashful virgins whom neither man nor jinnee will have touched before
  55,57,So which of your Lord‘s blessings would you deny
  55,58,Virgins as fair as corals and rubies
  55,59,So which of your Lord‘s blessings would you deny
  55,60,Shall the reward of goodness be anything but good
  55,61,So which of your Lord‘s blessings would you deny
  55,62,And beside these there shall be two other Gardens
  55,63,so which of your Lord‘s blessings would you deny
  55,64,of darkest green
  55,65,So which of your Lord‘s blessings would you deny
  55,66,A gushing fountain shall flow in each
  55,67,So which of your Lord‘s blessings would you deny
  55,68,"Each planted with fruit-trees, the palm and the pomegranate"
  55,69,So which of your Lord‘s blessings would you deny
  55,70,In each there shall be virgins chaste and fair
  55,71,So which of your Lord‘s blessings would you deny
  55,72,"Dark-eyed virgins, sheltered in their tents"
  55,73,so which of your Lord‘s blessings would you deny
  55,74,whom neither man nor jinnee will have touched before
  55,75,So which of your Lord‘s blessings would you deny
  55,76,They shall recline on green cushions and fine carpets
  55,77,So which of your Lord‘s blessings would you deny
  55,78,"Blessed be the name of your Lord, the Lord of Majesty and Glory"